MOTORISTS are advised to be aware of traffic disruptions expected on Friday, 17 February, in the Sandton precinct due to the memorial service of slain hip-hop star Kiernan “AKA” Forbes. The service for the late Lemonade hitmaker will take place at the Sandton Convention Centre from 3pm to 6pm. Johannesburg Metropolitan Police Department (JMPD) officers will be deployed to control and implement partial road closures around the centre and roads affected. JMPD spokesman Xolani Fihla said the following roads would be closed: • Maude and Fifth streets • Maude and West streets • Alice and Fifth streets • West and Katherine streets • West and Rivonia Road • West and Duodar streets “Motorists are further advised to acquaint themselves with traffic management for the day, and be patient during the duration of the service,” Fihla said in a statement. REGISTER TO COMMENT! AKA will be laid to rest in a private provincial funeral on Saturday, 18 February.